title: Don't observe when observe tool isn't selected
message:
Don't observe when observe tool isn't selected

This means that you can take voice transcription notes without
interference from the decibel sensor except when recording.

More generally, take the framework from CameraFragment
that detects when a tool fragment is active, and make it available
to all of the tool fragments.

title: Don't try to chop to half-size if the JPG is rotated.
message:
Don't try to chop to half-size if the JPG is rotated.

Samsung Edge, and some other Samsung phones, it appears,
store the captured JPEGs rotated, with EXIF metadata defining
their orientation.  Without unrotating the image, chopping
them results in weirdness.

I've written code that first rotates them, and then
chops them, but that OOMs.  It should be possible to do
the rotation and crop as one matrix operation, but I
don't seem to have quite the cleverness I need to get that
done right now.

This solution is not-quite-right, but has the advantage
of not being very, very wrong.

title: Merge "Two tactics for dealing with failed writes in UserMetadataManager."
message: Merge "Two tactics for dealing with failed writes in UserMetadataManager."

title: Two tactics for dealing with failed writes in UserMetadataManager.
message:
Two tactics for dealing with failed writes in UserMetadataManager.

Save what was in the file before writing, just in case writing fails,
to avoid having the file empty and losing all the data.

UserMetadataManager caches UserMetadata in the same way ExperimentCache
caches experiments. It will write to file no more than once every 500ms.
This reduces file-writing load.

title: Remove logic and UI for switching experiments during observe
message:
Remove logic and UI for switching experiments during observe

Experiment-loading logic was unnecessarily complex because we still had
code that believed that the active experiment could change out from
under the observe UI.

This should make it much harder to enter a no-drawer state.

This also makes the sensor registry responsible for excluded sensors,
and moves some logic around sound permissions from MainActivity to
PanesActivity, although not all sound permissions bugs are resolved.

title: RecorderController is a main-process shared object
message:
RecorderController is a main-process shared object

The goal is that RecorderController lives in the main process, and
can be accessed by activities and services; we'll have a global state
Behavior<RecordingStatus> that will be updated by RecorderController,
and can be subscribed by others.

There should be no behavior changes in this CL, just removing an
unused layer of indirection.

title: Create a DataService.
message:
Create a DataService.

Over time, the goal is to use this service for global data and services,
rather than getting those from a static AppSingleton that any activity
can access.

To begin with, activities and fragments can bind to this service, which
under the hood, serves up the same old AppSingleton.  But once everyone
is using DataService, we can eliminate the global AppSingleton in favor
of one managed directly by the service.

Otherwise, hoping that docs directly on the class answer questions.

Move spinner management out of RecordFragment

The activity that manages RecordFragment should control how to
respond to recording events and experiment changes, rather than
allowing RecordFragment to muck about in the activity's view

This is the first step of several; next we'll give the actionbar

a different activity (for the new paned activity, for example)
without making so many assumptions about the activity's UI

title: Merge "Pool objects to prevent clobbering and over-allocation."
message: Merge "Pool objects to prevent clobbering and over-allocation."

title: Pool objects to prevent clobbering and over-allocation.
message:
Pool objects to prevent clobbering and over-allocation.

This uses a pool of reusable SensorMessage objects to make sure:

1) Each set of sensor values is delivered exactly once to the observer
   (Fixing a bug where previously one observation could clobber the
   previous one and display the same value twice)

2) Many sensor readings can be observed with zero allocations once
   the queue is primed.

In a scenario where 5 sensor cards in graph mode are displayed on Moto E,
this is the memory allocation improvement:

Before: Each second: 10,600 allocations totalling 397kB
After:  Each second:  7,500 allocations totalling 274kB

This fixes the zoom issue but the seekbar thumb may be drawn in the
wrong place if it was way offscreen during the last crop and we are
resuming cropping. It doesn't impact where the RunReviewOverlay draws
the vertical line, the selected crop point, or the ability for the user

correctly, so it feels lower priority and is tricky to debug.
I'll tackle it separately.

title: Updates to views and layouts to support large screens.
message:
Updates to views and layouts to support large screens.

RunReview, Exp Details and Project Details now have a max width,
as does the Learn More page.

In addition: the Meter Mode stats view was changed so that it
can grow into large screens and shrink to small screens without
issue. The Project Details and Exp. Details pages had their
description / archived section updated to allow for an element
overlap per new mocks, and to center the text and archived
indicators. Because of the overlap, they can no longer be
transparent when archived, so now archived color state is
handled slightly differently.

This does not address the tutorial page.

title: Add option to delay stopping a sensor to avoid churn.
message:
Add option to delay stopping a sensor to avoid churn.

[For review from a design and functionality point of view.]

[If we like it, should I put it behind a testing option?]

Another option for the start/stop churn for API sensors.

This option is close to Justin's suggestion: when we ask
sensors to stop, we wait for N seconds to see if they are
re-started, before finally stopping.

RecorderController is the object that will eventually move
to the sensor service, so this is the right direction to
move toward the service solution.

title: Fix bug where playing note then rest then same note didn't play note second time.
message:
Fix bug where playing note then rest then same note didn't play note second time.

The state machine underlying rest detection wasn't resetting the prevIndex
to its default value.  Since the prevIndex wasn't reset, when the new note
(of the same index) needed to be played, it was erroneously suppressed.

decimal to display, and is now in charge of a sensor's value's

version.

and resize based on the text inside of them.

message:
First set of changes toward new Discoverer API

For the new manage devices screen, ExternalSensorDiscoverers can't
assume that they're talking directly to a preference screen, so
this creates a ConnectableSensor model class for a ListAdapter
to be used later.

Also, corrects a bug in ScalarInputSpec, which had the possibility
of confusing two sensors from different providers with the same
address.

title: Adjust text size of live meter text when large font is on.
message:
Adjust text size of live meter text when large font is on.

This stops the units from being cropped in large text mode,
and fixes an accessibility problem.

Also increases the card min height to 260dp, which will help
smaller screens and large fonts to crop less when there are
too many lines of descriptive text. The previous value, 240dp,
was derived from adding heights in this spec:
https://folio.googleplex.com/scinotebook/Mock/Sensor%20card/Latest#%2FGraphic%20Card_spec.jpg
It was not itself spec'ed out. Adding another 20dp of height
allows us buffer for 3 lines of text or small screens. Tested
on a Moto X and a Nexus 6, this seems reasonable.

new code. Instead, functionality was moved around and old

* Loading data when scrolling forwards and backwards (from ScalarSensor)

(LineGraphPresenter, SensorDataRenderer, GraphData, etc)
